{"id":"1603.02268","submitter":"Oren Wiezel","authors":"Oren Wiezel and Yizhar Or","title":"Optimization and small-amplitude analysis of Purcell's three-link\n  microswimmer model","comments":"Accepted to \"Royal Society, Proceedings A\"","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1098/rspa.2016.0425","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.flu-dyn","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  This work studies the motion of Purcell's three-link microswimmer in viscous\nflow, by using perturbation expansion of its dynamics under small-amplitude\nstrokes. Leading-order expressions and next-order correction terms for the\ndisplacement of the swimmer are obtained for the cases of a square or circular\ngait in the plane of joint angles. The correction terms demonstrate the\nreversal in movement direction for large stroke amplitudes, which has\npreviously only been shown numerically. In addition, asymptotic expressions for\nLighthill's energetic efficiency are obtained for both gaits. These\napproximations enable calculating optimal stroke amplitudes and swimmer's\ngeometry (i.e. ratio of links' lengths) for maximizing either the displacement\nor Lighthill's efficiency.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Mar 2016 13:59:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 3 Apr 2016 14:48:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 8 Aug 2016 13:15:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-28"}
